steps.detail:
Function `async def log_event_stream(subscriber_queue: asyncio.Queue, filter_decision: str | None, filter_service_id: str | None) -> AsyncGenerator[str, None]`. In an infinite loop: (1) `event = await asyncio.wait_for(subscriber_queue.get(), timeout=15.0)` — timeout sends a keep-alive comment `: keepalive

`. (2) Apply filters: skip event if `filter_decision` set and `event.decision != filter_decision`. (3) Skip if `filter_service_id` set and `event.service_id != filter_service_id`. (4) Serialize event to JSON (pre-redacted by SentinelLogger — no additional processing needed). (5) Yield `f'data: {json_str}

'` (SSE format). On `asyncio.CancelledError`: break loop and trigger cleanup.
